        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 7:20AM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 718 AM CDT, mesonet stations reported gusty southeast winds to 45
mph along a line extending from near Onaka to near Cottonwood Lake
Near Agar to Canning. These winds are occurring as the precipitation
from the showers and thunderstorms comes to an end. Movement was
east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Highmore, Faulkton, Blunt, Harrold, Brentwood Colony, Evergreen
Colony, Cresbard, Stephan, Orient, Ree Heights, Seneca, Chelsea,
Devoe, Onaka, Thunderbird Colony, Miranda, Polo, Stone Lake,
Burkmere, and South Scatterwood Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
